Package de.rwth.swc.coffee4j.junit.provider.configuration.reporter

Interface ReporterProvider

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ExtensionContextBasedProvider<java.util.Collection<ExecutionReporter>>
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.
    @FunctionalInterface
public interface ReporterProvider
extends ExtensionContextBasedProvider<java.util.Collection<ExecutionReporter>>
    An ReporterProvider is responsible for providing an arbitrary number of ExecutionReporter implementations (even none is allowed) for a CombinatorialTest.

    To register a ReporterProvider, use the ReporterSource annotation as demonstrated by Reporter.

    Implementations must provide a no-args constructor.

    This is more or less a copy of ArgumentsProvider from the junit-jupiter-params project.
